Angry Seshego residents burned a shack that is believed to be one of the hideouts of the gangs at night. The shack is closer to two houses belonging to the Burial 13 gang group members. They apparently smoke drugs inside the shack and wait for innocent people to rob them. Residents also went to several houses were the suspected criminals stay to send a string message to their parents EFF leader Jossey Buthane calmed angry residents and further requested not to harm three boys believed to be of burial 13 gang group after the meeting to show them their other hiding places. "Please, let us allow them to take us to all their hiding places so that can be destroyed. We can't live in fear in our own kadi because of young criminals. We must end all this kinds of criminal elements in Seshego. Enough is enough." said Buthane.